### Part VII — In the editor

A loom is several languages at once — the Loom syntax, the prose, and the code in each section's language — and this part gives each of them a real editor. Loom projects the document into a tree of virtual files and hands it to the editor through one plugin and a language server.

1. The virtual-code projection
2. The symbol-capability registry
3. The projection pass
4. The Loom language plugin
